3 A clustering-based approach to a static scheduling of
multiple workflows with soft deadlines
The essence of a clustering-based approach is that the planning process is divided into three main
stages: (i) clustering â€“ a creation of groups (clusters) of tasks, (ii) ordering â€“ a search for consistent
order of clusters, and (iii) scheduling â€“ a search for final mapping of tasks on resources for all clusters
according to the order. Here, we introduce a new algorithm for scheduling multiple workflows with
soft deadlines, which is denoted as MDW-C (Multiple Deadline-constrained Workflows â€“ Clusteringbased). In MDW-C, we use a definition of the subdeadline d ij for the j -th task of the i -th workflow

